      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EGO BALE (8) hit the ground running from the squeeze draw with a slick early split, holding on for a minor placing when third and beaten 3 lengths at Warrnambool over 390m in 22.63. Makes plenty of appeal. MAJOR ENVY (1) has an honest record despite remaining a maiden after 31 starts. Was third (18.06) at Mt Gambier latest and although yet to win tends to go well here. Still to record a win from this draw but has never missed the frame in two starts. Overdue and gets his chance. RAPID BURST (3) filled a minor placing last start at this track behind Adrenaline Burst (22.59) in a Rank Limit - Restricted Win. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Expecting another good run. SUPER STITCH (7) continues to race well and is sure to be competitive again.",
